#N0.50#########################################################################
DATA,80,"Undervoltage trip selection",0,1,0,2
	"When '0'(NO) is selected, the motor is not tripped at insufficient voltage. If voltage should fall "
	"and undervoltage status is found while the motor is running, the motor stops after running free, "
	"while if operation instruction is input after recovery of power, the motor is restarted automatically. (*Be cautious.) "
	"When '1'(YES) is selected, the motor is tripped at undervoltage, and trip signal is output."
#N0.51#########################################################################
DATA,81,"Retrial selection",0,4,0,2
	"0: No retrial.     1 - 4: Number of retrials"
	"Automatic reset in trip (trip retrial) can be set here."
	"Trip can be is automatically reset to allow operation to continue.Use this function only "
	"on such equipment that has no problem of safety even if the motor is automatically restarted."
#N0.52#########################################################################
DATA,82,"Retrial start time",1,120,0,2
	"You can set waiting time until retrial operation is performed after trip is found."
	"You can set 1 to 120 seconds. "
